stylometry: Transportation problem is a problem when you are shipping something from point A to point B.  A transshipment problem is simalar to a tranprotation problem except it consists of things called nodes.  Nodes are places where products can be shipped.  Arcs and flows are also used in these problems because an arc is how different one is from the other, and a flow is just as it sounds where and how the product will flow or go to each destination.  An example of a transshipment problem would be if you owned say a UPS, and you wanted to figure out what the nodes, arcs, and flows are to give you the shorts distance to a site.  This will allow you to switch up things such as trucks, routes, drivers and so on.  When doing the transshipment problem you will find out how to maximize your profit by puting the right trucks, drivers, and using the right routes to limit the time and/or gas.
